comments.text:
Donny was a good bowler, and a good man. He was...he was one of us. He was 
a man who loved the outdoors, and bowling, and as a surfer he explored the 
beaches of southern California from La Jolla to Leo Carillo, and up to 
Pismo. He died.. he died as so many young men of his generation before his 
time, and in your wisdom, Lord, you took him. Just as you took so many 
bright, flowering young men at Khe San, and Lan Doc, and Hill 364. These 
young men gave their lives, and so did Donny. Donny who loved bowling. And 
so, Theodore Donald Karabotsos.. in accordance with what we think your 
dying wishes might well have been....we commit your final mortal remains to 
the bosom of the Pacific Ocean, which you loved so well. Goodnight, sweet 
prince.
